at|All suit responses at the 4-level and higher other than Gerber 4@C are undefined in the SAYC bidding system. You should avoid using these bids unless you have discussed them thoroughly with your regular partner. If your partner responds to your 1NT opening with an undefined bid, your best course of action is to pass (and to discuss his bid when the current deal is finished).

|
pg| ***** 79 ***** |


at|The SAYC bidding system does not attempt to define every possible bidding sequence after a 1NT opening bid. Some bridge players and partnerships delight in trying to do just that (and not only after 1NT). 

If you do this in an intelligent manner, you can improve your bidding system, but most bridge players find that there is a point where the benefits of increased bidding accuracy are outweighed by the burden of having to remember the meanings of obscure bids that rarely arise in practice. 

It is really up to each partnership to find a comfortable medium that is maximally effective for them. SAYC is designed to be that medium for the average partnership.

|
