|cp||at|At the beginning of this topic we reviewed some of the issues involved in deciding on whether or not a convention should be added into a bidding system. One of the main dangers of using conventions is:

|
pg| ***** 81 ***** |


cs|2|At|^-{ Replacing a natural bid with an artificial bid 
 means that the natural bid is no longer available. }
^-
|
pg| ***** 82 ***** |


cs|4|at|^-{ For a convention to be effective, the gain from using that convention must be 
 greater than the loss that comes from replacing a natural bid with an artificial bid. }
^-|
