n#|8|
at|In the case of Jacoby transfer bids, the 2@D response to a 1NT opening bid (which would be a signoff in diamonds in the absence of transfers) is used artificially as a transfer to hearts. 

While most bridge authorities believe that giving up this natural bid is a small price to pay for the use of Jacoby transfers, the fact remains that the responder to a 1NT opening bid will sometimes want to sign off in diamonds (or clubs for that matter).

|
