nt|^b@2^z@3
While Jacoby transfer bids are often used on hands with 6-card or longer major suits, it is also perfectly acceptable to invoke Jacoby with a hand that contains a 5-card major. The 2@S, 3@C, and 3@D responses to 1NT should not be used with hands that contain a 5-card minor:

|
pg| ***** 96 ***** |


cs|1|at|^-{ When the responder bids 2@S, 3@C, or 3@D, he promises at least 6 cards in his long minor. }
^-
