at|In the SAYC bidding system, the 3@H and 3@S responses to a 1NT opening bid have similar meanings as they do in most other bidding systems that do not use Jacoby transfer bids:

|
pg| ***** 99 ***** |


cs|3|at|^-{ SAYC uses the direct 3@H and 3@S responses to a 1NT opening to suggest at least 6 
 cards in the suit that was bid and a hand that is strong enough to be interested in slam. }
^-
|
pg| ***** 100 ***** |


cs|2|At|^-{ When the responder to a 1NT opening has a 5-card (or longer) major, he almost always 
 responds with a Jacoby transfer. The 3@H and 3@S responses are an exception to this. }
^-
