at|A better way to escape from 1NT would be to try to sign off in 3@D via a 2@S response. While this course of action might improve the contract, it might also make things worse. You really should have a 6-card minor suit in order to invoke the 2@S convention. Unbalanced hands with 5-card minors tend to play better in 1NT than they do at the 3-level of the minor.

